 Japan.\n* This is the first appearance of a male {{p|Garchomp}} in the {{pkmn|anime}}.\n* This is the first time multiple [[Mega Evolution|Mega Evolved]] Pokémon are featured simultaneously in the anime.\n* This episode marks the first appearance of a number of Pokémon species in the anime after long absences:\n** {{p|Blastoise}}, who last appeared in \'\'[[DP091|One Team, Two Team, Red Team, Blue Team!]]\'\'.\n** {{p|Kangaskhan}}, who last appeared in \'\'[[DP100|Aiding the Enemy!]]\'\'.\n** {{p|Absol}} and {{p|Manectric}}, both of whom last appeared in \'\'[[M12|Arceus and the Jewel of Life]]\'\'.\n** {{p|Alakazam}}, who last appeared in \'\'[[DP140|Historical Mystery Tour!]]\'\'.\n** {{p|Scizor}}, who last appeared in \'\'[[DP154|Mastering Current Events!]]\'\'.\n** {{p|Venusaur}} and {{p|Aerodactyl}}, both of whom last appeared in \'\'[[M13|Zoroark: Master of Illusions]]\'\'.\n* This episode marks the debut of {{m|Blast Burn}} in the anime.\n** With this, all [[Move variations|variations]] of {{m|Hyper Beam}} have been featured in the anime.\n* This is the first time {{m|Toxic}} has been used by a non-{{type|Poison}} Pokémon in the anime.\n* Excluding [[Pikachu short]]s, this is the first dubbed special not narrated by [[Rodger Parsons]] or [[Mike Pollock]].\n* Mairin references {{Ash}} and the events of \'\'[[XY002|Lumiose City Pursuit!]]\'\'.\n* Excluding flashbacks, this episode marks the only time Alain has been seen losing a battle with another {{pkmn|Trainer}}.\n\n===Errors===\n* In the flashback in which {{an|Professor Sycamore}} appears, his female Garchomp has a cut on her fin, a male-only trait.\n* In the credits of the English dub, [[Astrid]]\'s voice actress, [[Kate Bristol]], is incorrectly credited as "Kate Briston".\n\n===Dub edits===\n* In the Hindi dub, the intro scene with the multiple Mega Evolved Pokémon and the title card was skipped, and the episode started directly from the scene after the title card.\n\n==In other languages==\n{{Epilang|